description: Don’t like the black one? How about silver? Don’t wait until spring when the price goes up and they are hard to find at a reasonable price. The sun and warm weather is not too far away!

This is a great little ’79 Super Beetle that runs and drives just like brand new. One of only 10,681 convertibles were built by Karman in this last year of production and they remain a sought after yet enjoyable collector car today with at strong market value.

It is powered by a 1585cc dual carbureted engine with manual 4-speed transmission that shifts ultra smooth. The engine just went through a partial rebuild where the heads were ported, SCAT 1.4 ratio rocker arms and new chrome push rods were installed. It is freshly tuned up, the fluids all changed and valves adjusted. This is a quick and fun little Bug that is ready to go!

The body is in good shape and painted in silver with a black interior. It sits on 15? steel wheels with caps and like-new tires. It has had recent scheduled maintenance done including a full tune-up and runs great. The top is new in sedan style and operates just as it should.
It has the original Blaupaunkt radio which works great.
The vehicle is a believed to be an only 46,500 original mile example. Financing available.
